<header>
	
		
		Read this sample answer to the writing task in the last exercise and find the mistakes. There are 15. Click on them.
		
</header>
	
<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../media/DD_AW_005.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><br/><ol id="questionList"></ol>
</section>
<section id="fb1">
	<p align="left"><b>example -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>such</b><font color="#000000"></font></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb2">
	<p align="left"><b>Consequently -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>However</b><b>:</b> 'Consequently' means 'as a result'.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb3">
	<p align="left"><b>support -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>believe</b><b>:</b> 'Support' should be followed with a noun or gerund, but not with another verb clause.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb4">
	<p align="left"><b>really -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>highly</b><b>:</b> 'really' is too informal.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb5">
	<p align="left"><b>In contrast -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>In fact</b></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb6">
	<p align="left"><b>probably -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>likely</b><font color="#000000"></font></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb7">
	<p align="left"><b>probable -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>certain</b><b>:</b> 'almost certain' means 'probable'. 'Almost probable' doesn't make sense.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb8">
	<p align="left"><b>as -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>like</b><b>:</b> We can say 'such as' or 'like' when giving examples.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb9">
	<p align="left"><b>believe -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>support</b><b>:</b> evidence can be used to 'support' an argument.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb10">
	<p align="left"><b>possibility -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>probability</b><b>:</b> This is an expression.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb11">
	<p align="left"><b>reason -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>claim</b><b>:</b> In other words, 'it is also argued that...'</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb12">
	<p align="left"><b>Despite -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>Nevertheless</b><b>:</b> 'Despite' must be followed with a noun, a gerund or the word 'this'.</font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb13">
	<p align="left"><b>as instance -></b><font color="#0000ff"><b> for instance</b></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb14">
	<p align="left"><b>believed -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>convinced</b><font color="#000000"></font></font></p>
</section>
<section id="fb15">
	<p align="left"><b>must -> </b><font color="#0000ff"><b>could</b><b>:</b> 'Must' can't be used to speculate about the future.</font></p>
</section>
